# Event Class Structure

Events (NPCs) extend `RpgEvent`, use `@EventData`, and implement `onInit` and `async onAction(player: RpgPlayer)`.

```typescript
@EventData({
    name: 'EV-001',
    hitbox: { width: 32, height: 16 }
})
export default class MyEvent extends RpgEvent {
    onInit() {
        this.setGraphic('graphicName')
        this.setHitbox(32, 16)
    }

    async onAction(player: RpgPlayer) {
        // Interaction logic
    }
}
```

- Use unique, descriptive event IDs (e.g. `EV-TOWN-VILLAGER-001`).
- Set graphic and hitbox in `onInit`; use `async onAction` for player interactions and `await player.showText()` etc.
